- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and semantics. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses different compositional models of distributional meaning. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with the development of a calculus to deal with copying of linguistic resources. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the development of a calculus and models for natural language processing. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with the analysis of ambiguous elliptical phrases.
